      "message": "xyz.openbmc_project.Logging.Create is now deprecated:\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-logging/blob/master/README.md#deprecated-methods-for-creating-event-logs\n\nThe preferred approach is to define the event in PDI YAML and use lg2::commit(EventClass(...)). This also avoids encoding metadata into the message string, which is discouraged by:\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/anti-patterns.md#ill-defined-data-structuring-in-lg2-message-strings\n\nIf we still want to use this API, could the XID number, sequence, etc. be passed via additionalData using REDFISH_MESSAGE_ID / REDFISH_MESSAGE_ARGS so bmcweb can map this to a Redfish event registry entry?",
